commit message:
Added the ability to show the database of profiles
- Also moved AccountManager into passwordmaker-je-lib as I think it would be useful in other places, and its faster to unit test there
- Made build system do an auto versioning for the android display version.  Based on the git tags.
Modified the proguard rules so that it doesn't obfuscate
Intellij keeps modifying my build file behind my back.  Adding back in the mavenLocal() directive.

Adding favorites into the mix
- Also improved the ActivityBar so that it doesn't need a menu for phones around the size of a nexus 4 and larger.  Probably smaller too, but if it overflow it should create a menu for the actions.
- Added some sample favorites for development is easy
- Made favorites use this autocomplete thing, that does a 'matching substring' filter
- Favorites are now swipe to delete.
Reorganized the filling of the fields .
Adding ability to modify patterns for profiles.
Got part of the import/export feature ready.  However, it seems to be failing to load it all.  Maybe I should use the resulting XML as a unit test for the pwm library.
Adding the ability to add patterns, autocomplete urls from accounts, modify the account url field.
